            "Market Penetration: Selling more of your existing products to your existing market. This is the safest approach, often achieved by lowering prices, increasing distribution, or ramping up promotional support",
            "Market Development: Taking your existing products and introducing them to new markets. This includes targeting new demographics or expanding geographically"
        ],
        "BULLET":[
            "Product Development: Launching new products to your existing market base. This involves R&D to meet unaddressed needs of your current customers.",
            "Diversification: Developing new products for new markets. This is the riskiest but potentially highest-reward strategy, often requiring mergers or acquisitions."
        ]
    }        
},

